name: GoogLeNet for Image Classification
full_description: GoogLeNet, also known as Inception v1, is a deep convolutional neural network designed for image classification tasks. It was developed by Google and achieved significant success in the ImageNet Large Scale Visual Recognition Challenge (ILSVRC) 2014.
keywords: image classification, deep learning, GoogLeNet, Google, Inception
author: swithana

ai_model.name: GoogLeNet
ai_model.description: A deep convolutional neural network model for classifying images.
